---
title: Bruschetta Zucchini Boats with Couscous & Melty Mozz
description: Send your taste buds on a flavorful cruise—a yacht to Yumtown, if you will—with this crowd-pleasing stuffed zucchini. These boats are filled with supremely savory couscous that’s studded with tomatoes, Italian seasoning, and garlic. They’re blanketed in a layer of melty mozzarella, then topped with bruschetta and a drizzle of balsamic glaze. We gotta say, there’s something about this recipe that’ll really put the wind back in your sails.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6076d4f3170cf01453212d38-e1fc5c37.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/bruschetta-zucchini-boats-6076d4f3170cf01453212d38-08507f9c.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Italian
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 640 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 760 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/bruschetta-zucchini-boats-6076d4f3170cf01453212d38
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{2}; scoop out seeds with a #spoon{} and discard. Rub
each half all over with a drizzle of @olive oil{7%tsp}; season with half the
@Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.
Arrange cut sides down on a #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While zucchini roasts, peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Finely dice
@Roma tomato{2}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
@Israeli couscous{3/4%cup}, garlic, half the tomatoes, and remaining Italian
seasoning. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and
a big pinch of salt. Bring to a simmer, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook
until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Drain any excess liquid from #pot{} if necessary.

While couscous cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}
(save the rest for serving), remaining tomatoes, a large drizzle of olive oil,
and @balsamic glaze{5%tsp} to taste (save a bit for serving if desired). Season
with salt, pepper, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste.

Season couscous with salt and pepper.

Remove zucchini from oven and heat broiler to high. Flip zucchini; blot out any
excess liquid with #paper towels{}. Stuff zucchini with as much couscous as
will fit (save the rest for serving). Sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide remaining couscous between plates and top with stuffed zucchini. Top with
bruschetta and drizzle with any remaining balsamic glaze to taste. Garnish with
remaining Parmesan. Sprinkle with a pinch of chili flakes if desired and serve.